feat(brand): implement canonical Synapse v2 brand system

Reconciles the running app with the brand handoff at
docs/design_handoff_brand/. The handoff defines the canonical Synapse v2
mark, lockups, icon set, and applications; the codebase had a partial
Synapse v2 implementation but the mark itself was geometrically wrong
(closed concentric circles + diagonal axon on a 32-unit viewBox vs. the
canonical three open arcs + horizontal read-line into a node on a
64-unit viewBox).

Mark + lockups (Phase 1)
- Rewrite SvMark.tsx in place with the canonical three-arc + read-line
  geometry. Every existing render site (top bar, dashboard overlays,
  side rail) inherits the new shape automatically.
- Add Wordmark, MarkMono, MarkAnimated, and four Lockup* components.
- Add engSpin / engBlink keyframes alongside the existing svSpin family.

Custom 30-icon set (Phase 2)
- New frontend/src/app/components/icons/ -- Ico base + 8 status + 8 media
  + 14 action/nav icons, 24-unit viewBox, 1.5px stroke, round caps.
- Drop the inner SVG title element in favor of aria-label on the svg
  element; the inner title would otherwise be matched by Playwright text
  selectors (cleared 14 E2E failures in one fix) and could be spoken
  twice by some screen readers.
- Migrate brand-meaningful Lucide callers (StateIndicator,
  MediaTypeBadge, ActionButtons, TrackGrid, MatchingVisualizer,
  DiscCard, SvTopBar, ReviewQueue, ReIdentifyModal, NamePromptModal,
  HistoryPage, EnhanceWizard) to the new Ico components. Lucide stays
  for utility primitives (chevrons, save, trash, X-for-close, plus) per
  the brand-vs-utility rule documented in docs/development/brand.md.

Splash + AppIcon (Phase 3)
- Inline pre-React HTML splash in index.html -- visible during initial
  bundle parse, fades when main.tsx mounts (CSS class on html element,
  JS removes it to trigger the transition).
- React Splash component wired into App.tsx behind a 2.5s grace period
  so brief WebSocket blips don't flash the overlay.
- AppIcon component with dark + light editions, Apple-HIG squircle
  radius, ring grid, scanlines, corner ticks, v1 stamp at >=96px.

Asset export pipeline (Phase 4)
- scripts/render-svg-sources.mjs + scripts/generate-brand-assets.mjs.
- npm run brand:export rasterizes with sharp and packs cross-platform
  .ico and .icns with png2icons -- no iconutil dependency. Emits 21
  artifacts under frontend/public/brand/ (favicons + Windows .ico +
  macOS .icns + iconset + Linux PNGs + manifest.json).
- Wire favicon links in index.html to the new SVG + .ico fallbacks.
- Delete obsolete frontend/public/disc.svg and engram.svg.

ConfigWizard alignment (Phase 5)
- Tokenize ConfigWizard.css to consume --color-sv-* CSS custom
  properties; drop the duplicate scanline overlay (handoff says resist
  over-glow); move form-group labels from magenta to cyan-dim per the
  magenta-is-action rule; match SvPanel chrome (1px line, sharp corners,
  no inner border).

Docs + tooling (Phase 6)
- New docs/development/brand.md -- developer reference covering tokens,
  primitive locations, the brand-vs-utility icon rule, the asset
  pipeline, and accepted deviations from the original plan.
- README.md gets a Brand Identity section linking the handoff.
- CLAUDE.md updates the dashboard description and adds brand:export to
  Commands.
- docs/engram.svg regenerated with the new mark geometry.
- docs/design_handoff_synapse/README.md cross-references the brand
  handoff for clarity (the two handoffs are complementary, not
  redundant).
- mkdocs.yml nav adds the new development/brand.md.

Verification
- npm run build / npm run lint / npm run test:unit: clean
- backend pytest tests/unit: 624/624 pass
- backend pytest tests/integration: 83/83 pass (full disc lifecycle)
- playwright e2e: 69 passed, 6 skipped, 0 failed
- npm run brand:export: idempotent across two runs, 21 artifacts

